cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with channel state information (CSI) feedback and optimization of beam-vectors to maximize spectral efficiency, which are topics related to information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses a cloud radio access network (CRAN) and proposes a pilot scheduling algorithm, which are topics related to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper formulates a two-stage optimization problem and proposes a robust transmission design algorithm, which are topics related to systems and control. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper mentions high data rates, which are related to multimedia applications. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Although not a major focus of the paper, the proposed algorithms involve optimization and scheduling, which are topics related to artificial intelligence.
